<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-253-621  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 253 621.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Jan 9 1989 v8 n1 p23(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Pub. Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Qandamp;A is strong on simplicity and likes plain English. (SoftwareReview) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Symantec Corp's Qandamp;A Version 3.0 is a database management systemand word processing program that can provide information andgenerate reports using plain English commands.andP;  The $199 programoffers the user a vocabulary of standard terms which can be usedto quickly customize Qandamp;A, thus eliminating the need for complexsyntax or programming.andP;  The database allows a maximum 256M filesize, with 16 million records per file.andP;  Qandamp;A Reports can containup to 50 columns with 50 sort levels and a maximum width of 1,000characters.andP;  It is easy to set up a database form with the help ofthe program's context-sensitive help screens and menu commands.andO;One drawback is that a few professional word processing aremissing, but the program's ease-of-use, speed and power will morethan make up for the missing features.andP;  It is recommended for mostoffice users.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Symantec Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Q and A 3.0 (Data base management system).andO;Topic:     EvaluationSoftware PackagesData Base Management SystemsWord Processing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Qandamp;A Is Strong on Simplicity and Likes Plain EnglishandM;Qandamp;A is an integrated, network-ready database and word processing programwhose major strength is its ability to provide information and even generatereports without requiring esoteric commands.andM;The Intelligent Assistant is a natural-language interface that searches thedatabase and prepares reports with commands made in plain English.andP;  Startingwith a vocabulary of standard terms, a user can customize Qandamp;A quickly,eliminating the complex syntax or programming needed to use most databases.andM;The database allows a maximum 256M file size, with 16 million records perfile, 16,780 characters per record, 10 screens per form, seven differentinformation types and 512 sorting levels.andM;Qandamp;A reports can contain up to 50 columns with 50 sort levels and with amaximum width of 1,000 characters.andP;  You can specify 100 custom report formatsper database.andP;  Qandamp;A also does mailing labels, up to eight across.andM;Qandamp;A File can import from several formats, including Lotus 1-2-3 and dBaseIII.andP;  The program runs on computers with 512K RAM, but 640K and a hard diskare recommended.andM;It took me about 10 minutes to set up a database form without looking at thedocumentation; the context-sensitive help screens and menu commands wereenough.andM;The natural-language interface, which need not be used, is exceptional.andP;  Toaccess data you use the Intelligent Assistant and make requests in plainEnglish with no special syntax or codes.andP;  You just ask Qandamp;A questions in yournormal manner, for example, &quot;List all people living in San Francisco.&quot;andM;When the program finds a word it doesn't already know, you can either changeit to one the IA knows or simply add the new word to a list of synonyms, oryou can access the database directly by using more normal commands.andM;This is a large program and because of the amount of processing required torecognize natural language it is slow when using the Intelligent Assistant,but only while it is analyzing English language input.andM;Searching and report generation are quite fast.andM;Besides this database, Qandamp;A has a very good word processor, Write, completewith a 100,000-word spelling checker and support for Apple LaserWriter andHewlett-Packard LaserJet.andM;Write comes with many professional features, including undelete, row andcolumn math, and multiple columns.andP;  It has simple line drawing, a goodsearch-and-replace, easy-to-use mail merge and a good selection of formattingfeatures.andM;Write is missing a few professional word-processing features.andP;  But it issimple to learn, quite fast and will meet the needs of most office users.andM;A powerful, editable macro capability, which can be used throughout theprogram, is included.andP;  WordStar cursor commands are supported.andP;  The programcan export ASCII files and import from WordStar and other formats.andP;  The fast,in-memory editor is limited to 80 pages of text for a 640K machine.andP;  Maximumpage width is 250 characters.andM;Print queuing is available but not automatic; it must be programmed in.andP;  Thisis a simple procedure requiring you to create a short file containing thenames of each file to be printed.andM;Symantec now offers the word processor as a stand-alone product, Qandamp;A Write.andO;It has all the features of the Write module, except that on a 640K machine,files can be as large as 140 pages, or 160 pages with expanded memory.andP;  Italso includes a card file database for names and addresses.andM;Qandamp;A lets you run Lotus 1-2-3 or other programs directly from its main menu.andO;Although Qandamp;A lacks a spreadsheet, you can transfer data between 1-2-3 and thedatabase and place spreadsheets or graphs in documents.andM;As an integrated word processor and database, Qandamp;A is simple to learn and tooperate.andM;The Intelligent Assistant's ability to manipulate a database using commonterms makes it useful for situations in which many staff members will need touse the database.andO;</TEXT></DOC>